    "body": "<!-- .github/pull_request_template.md -->\r\n\r\n## 📌 Description\r\n\r\nThe comment at this location previously stated that only `float32` routing logits would be possible for blockscale MoE. However, it seems the launcher now supports bfloat16 for non-DS routing.\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n## Bug Fixes\n* Per-method routing precision handling updated: the model now selects routing tensor precision based on the chosen routing method (e.g., DeepSeekV3 uses higher-precision), replacing fixed per-path precision. This improves routing stability and consistency across routing configurations without changing public APIs.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
